  "prompt": "What is the formula of magnesium carbide?",
  "response": "The chemical formula for **magnesium carbide** is **Mg\u2082C\u2083**. This compound is also known as **magnesium sesquicarbide**. \n\n**Structure and Formation:**\n- **Mg\u2082C\u2083** consists of two magnesium (Mg) atoms combined with three carbon (C) atoms.\n- It is typically formed by reacting magnesium metal with carbon at high temperatures.\n\n**Applications:**\n- Magnesium carbide is used in producing acetylene gas upon reaction with water:\n  \\[\n  \\text{Mg}_2\\text{C}_3 + 6\\text{H}_2\\text{O} \\rightarrow 2\\text{Mg(OH)}_2 + 3\\text{C}_2\\text{H}_2\n  \\]\n- Acetylene generated from this reaction is utilized in welding and as a precursor in organic synthesis.\n\n**Safety Considerations:**\n- Like many carbides, magnesium carbide should be handled with care as it can react with moisture to release flammable gases.\n\n**Summary:**\n- **Magnesium Carbide Formula:** **Mg\u2082C\u2083**",
